{
  "text": "It also seemed to me that since Rob stated in the last session, the limit of the viewpoint is the source of all distortions, that the very nature of the service to self-distortions that create the left-hand path are a function of the veil, therefore, are dependent, you might say, to some degree, on at least a partial continued beginning. Does this make any sense? In what you suppose the polarities are both dependent upon a limited viewpoint. However, the negative polarity depends more heavily upon the illusory separation betwixt the self and all other mind, body, spirit, complexes. The positive a polarity attempts to see through the illusion to the Creator in each mind, body, spirit, complex, but for the greater part is concerned with behaviors and thoughts directed towards other selves in order to be of service. This attitude in itself is full of the stuff of your third density illusion.",
